<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1436,1210,1811]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,320,1210,1235]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Type material</emphasis>
not examined. 
<bibRefCitation box="[500,698,1210,1235]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" refId="ref37268" refString="Hancock, J. L. (1907 b) Studies of the Tetriginae (Orthoptera) in the Oxford University Museum. Transactions of the Entomological Society of London, 1907, 213 - 244, pl. 21." type="journal article">Hancock (1907b)</bibRefCitation>
wrote about two specimens of 
<emphasis box="[1063,1158,1210,1235]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Hancock" authorityYear="1907" box="[1063,1153,1210,1235]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Scelimena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="india">S. india</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
but without mentioning their sex. However, according to measurements provided (length of body entire, male 
<quantity box="[1120,1222,1246,1271]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.95" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="19.5">19.5 mm</quantity>
, pronotum 
<quantity box="[1350,1432,1247,1271]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="18.0">18 mm</quantity>
, posterior femora 
<quantity box="[351,421,1283,1307]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="7.0">7 mm</quantity>
) it is probable that those are two male syntypes. The type (or types?) are deposited in Philadelphia and according to OSF, there is a male holotype.
</paragraph>
